next - "Maintenance"
  Summary: variety per personality, uniform cause cascade, business rules enforced (alignment, personality, day/night), cause-consequence separation, slumber by species, mutant area swarm, outlaw massacre loot, stash by alignment, MCM regroup, freeze fix, performance
  Gameplay:
    Changed: alignment, personality, species, and the day/night cycle now control squad action consistently. Rule checks execute at the cause level before expensive world queries. The cause cascade reaches every applicable predicate per tick rather than terminating on the first few. Gating resides in the cause; action resides in the consequence. Each squad's identity (faction, species, active period, personality roll) determines its action. Faction and species behavior matches design intent rather than collapsing across categories.
    Changed: every cascade decision selects one specific action rather than a category. A campfire halt, a lair retreat, a stash fill, a surge-shelter slumber are independent rolls within the same drive. Variety emerges from cascade order across many small causes; handler-side filtering is no longer used.
    Added: mutant slumber differentiated by species. Cowardly mutants bed down in territory. Feral and predator species retreat to lairs. Aberrant and predator species seek surge shelters. Three distinct destinations under one drive.
    Added: mutant area swarm. Feral, predator, and aberrant squads claim empty smart terrains with additive spawn alongside the originals. Parallel to stalker conquest with its own cause and consequence; each tunes independently. The previous single Area Conquer consequence is now stalker conquer and mutant swarm.
    Changed: infestation relocated from mutant instincts to the area family. Trigger conditions unchanged. Predator and aberrant alpha squads continue to claim lair-type smarts and convert them into single-species nests via exclusive spawn replacement. Grouped with conquer and swarm under one MCM section with its own rate budget and gulag duration.
    Changed: post-conquest hold significantly reduced. Stalker conquerors and mutant swarm groups release smart terrains much sooner after arrival than the previous Area Conquer duration. Conquered territory turns over more frequently.
    Added: outlaw massacre loot. Bandits, renegades, and Greh route to massacre sites and strip corpses for weapons and gear, alongside the cowardly mutants that scavenge.
    Changed: work-shift causes gate on the day/night cycle, lifestyle causes do not. Stalkers run day-active work (trade, money harvest/hunt, outpost watches, exploration, research) and night-dormant survival (sleep, shelter). Eat, heal, rest, and socialize are any-hour -- nothing in the simulation says a squad cannot eat at night or take a halt during the day. Mutants follow species circadian rhythms; nocturnal species invert their active period.
    Changed: stash work partitioned by alignment. Outlaws ambush; neutral stalkers (Loner, Clear Sky, Freedom, Mercenary) loot; principled stalkers (Duty, Military, Monolith, ISG) and Ecologists fill. Each human faction now covers exactly one stash role.
    Changed: stash ambush is presence-only. The squad arrives at the stash, the cooldown timestamp resets on arrival, and no item action runs.
    Changed: stash fill items roll at arrival rather than at cause publish. Each fill draws independently; cause publish payload no longer carries item commitments.
    Changed: massacre scavenge narrows to cowardly mutants (Flesh, Zombie, Tushkano, Rat, Karlik). Outlaw scavenging migrated to the new Massacre Loot consequence.
    Changed: wounded hunt narrows to predator and aberrant mutants. Outlaws no longer participate.
    Changed: mutant instinct logic uses scent range exclusively. Eye-range checks removed. Scatter from higher-tier species and roam destinations both resolve via scent.
    Changed: personality floor lowered. The minimum chance applied to any personality roll dropped, so low-trait factions act less often on consequences they are poorly suited to. Faction differentiation across consequences widens accordingly.
    Changed: stash and area cooldowns operate as per-cause game-hour thresholds, replacing the previous wall-clock cooldown. Each sub-cause has its own threshold tunable in MCM; stash thresholds are shorter than area thresholds by default. Survives saves and time-acceleration changes.
    Removed: Squadkill Flee consequence. Squadkill now triggers only Squadkill Revenge; same-faction squads no longer flee to base after a wipe.
  News & Map:
    Added: news-chance slider on the News tab (0-100, default 20). Each consequence success rolls against the slider value before feeding the news pipeline. Higher values admit more events; lower values reduce frequency. Operates in addition to the existing compose-interval and scope throttles.
    Changed: news templates are per-consequence only. Multi-event composite templates (one entry covering both halves of a paired event) retired. Each consequence rolls its own news entry independently.
    Changed: PDA marker label reduced to two lines: action phrase and subject. Other-party identity moved into news template content.
    Fixed: five news templates assumed the PDA speaker shared the subject's faction (e.g. "I was with the Monolith patrol..."). Reworded to a neutral witness voice; any speaker can now voice any template without identity contradiction.
  MCM:
    Changed: cause sidebar consolidated from 11 pages to 4 (Reactions, Opportunities, Needs, Instincts). One page per category instead of one per cause.
    Changed: cause and consequence sections use one combined block per page: Cause, Description, Rules. Range and active period appear inside Rules. Internal identifiers no longer surface in user-facing strings; alignment and trait names render as plain English.
    Added: per-category cause budget sliders. Reactions, Needs, Instincts, Opportunities each carry their own counter; a busy category cannot starve another.
    Added: per-cause toggles and game-hour threshold sliders for stash and area. Each of the six sub-causes (loot, ambush, fill; conquer, swarm, infest) has its own pair.
    Added: Mutators tab consolidates territory conquest, infestation, alpha, and stalker rank mutators in one place. Cause and consequence sections now contain squad behavior only.
    Added: stash-ambush minimum-items slider. Determines whether outlaws ambush or loot a given stash.
    Added: Massacre Loot section under Consequences (toggle, rush, max squads).
    Removed: master umbrella toggles for needs, instincts, stash, and area. Per-cause toggles cover the same scope individually.
    Removed: drive-level enable toggles for needs and instincts. Each answer carries its own enable.
    Removed: per-cause and per-consequence personality min/max sliders. Replaced by a single global clamp applied to every personality roll.
  Compatibility:
    Added: save migration releases scripted squads whose on-arrive consequence no longer exists. Self-healing: zero orphans on a clean load makes the next pass a no-op.
  Fixed:
    Fixed: mutant area swarm publishes correctly. The cause was looking up its species table by faction key; aggressive mutant squads now claim empty smarts on arrival as designed. Dead since 1.5.0.
    Fixed: scripted squads no longer remain idle for the full pre-arrival hold when the engine has no real job slots at the destination. AP now verifies job allocation at arrival, filters out smarts authored without real patrol / sleep / work jobs at scan time, and re-checks during the wait so a precondition flip mid-hold (surge transition, day-to-night for sleepers, zombie state, trader running out of items) releases the squad cleanly.
    Fixed: alpha kill events no longer fire when the killer is a story NPC, trader, or named character. Aligns with the protection already applied to the alpha, wounded, and harvest causes.
    Fixed: Squadkill Revenge fires correctly on NPC-vs-NPC kills. The cause was publishing the wrong identifier field; the fix wires up the correct one. Dead since 1.5.0.
    Fixed: disabled or wrong-alignment radiant causes no longer consume a budget slot before the cheap gate runs. The cascade reaches every generator each tick rather than only the first few.
    Fixed: harvest haunt and wounded hunt no longer dispatch mutant squads with broken commander state into species-restricted consequences. Predator and aberrant species only.
    Fixed: late-bind cause registration runs synchronously. Mods that register their causes after the actor enters the world previously landed in storage but were never evaluated.
    Fixed: dropped the arrival-overflow path. The counter it relied on was sim-routing intent, not physical occupancy; squads with free job slots no longer eject on arrival.
    Fixed: peaceful destination causes (supply_trader, money_harvest, money_hunt, job_research) now exclude hostile-faction smarts. Without an enemy-relation gate, dynamic faction relations (e.g. Warfare flipping CSky vs ISG) routed restocking squads into hostile bases. Issue #7.
    Fixed: stash loot, ambush, and fill no longer route the squad into a hostile base. The post-stash destination smart was picked as the nearest smart to the stash with no relation filter; an enemy-faction filter now mirrors the peaceful-needs gate.
    Fixed: mutant species and faction display strings render lowercase in PDA news ("zombies" instead of "Zombies"). Capitalized common nouns mid-sentence read like UI labels; lowercase reads as prose. Issue #8.
    Fixed: zombified factions no longer trigger human-narrative news templates ("watch rotation", "laid out a rotation"). The area cause now routes humans (alignment_human, excludes zombified) and mutants (species feral/predator/aberrant, excludes zombie species) on separate paths; zombies fall through both. Issue #9 (resolved by 1d49fc7).
  Performance:
    Changed: cascade buffer shuffles in place. The previous code allocated a new array per tick; the new code swaps entries in the existing buffer. Per-tick allocation eliminated for the radiant cascade.
    Changed: radiant scan budget consolidated onto a single keyed counter. Cheap rule checks (toggle, alignment, personality, period) no longer consume slots reserved for world queries; the budget bounds the expensive operation only.
    Changed: scripted-squad scan checks lifetime before reasserting the target. The previous order reasserted on entries about to expire. One xsquad call saved per expiring entry per scan.
  Modder API:
    Added: ap_core_hud.register_identity_source(fn), register_subject_resolver(fn). Ext-registered at on_game_start; core holds zero ext imports.
    Added: ap_ext_tracker.get_alpha_marker_squads() - squad ids hosting alphas, for the HUD identity source.
    Added: ap_ext_util.get_faction_display(faction), get_species_display(species). Shared HUD/news translation path.
    Added: CAUSE_CATEGORY enum in ap_ext_const (REACTIONS, NEEDS, INSTINCTS, OPPORTUNITIES). Each cause declares its category for rate-limit grouping.
    Added: HARVEST_CALLBACKS, WOUNDED_CALLBACKS in ap_core_const. Cause registers once per family member with the same predicate.
    Added: REACTIVE_MAX_CONSEQUENCES_PER_CAUSE in ap_core_const. Consumer-enforced cap; safety net for future families.
    Added: ap_core_debug.bracket(constant). Log-label helper from CAUSE / CONSEQUENCE / TRACE constants; renames propagate.
    Added: ap_ext_common module. Chase pattern (move_actor_chasers, make_move_smart_chasers, make_on_arrive); used by harvest_rob, alphakill_targeted, squadkill_revenge.
    Changed: ap_ext_news.record_event(squad, cause, consequence, opts) -> add(...). add_unfiltered(...) bypasses the chance gate. opts.cause_id removed.
    Changed: ap_core_producer.register(name, config, handler) -> register(config, handler). config requires callback, cause_type, category, name. Dedup by handler reference.
    Changed: ap_core_limiter.check_cause_rate_limit(name) -> (key, max). Caller supplies key and cap.
    Changed: ap_ext_util.check_personality opts drops p_min / p_max. Reads global PERSONALITY_FLOOR / CEILING from ap_ext_const.
    Removed: ap_core_broker activity record API (record, get_record, get_records, clear_record, RECORD_CAPACITY). News owns its FIFO; HUD reads scripted-squad and identity registers.
    Removed: opts.cause_id and result._cause_id on cause/consequence payloads. Used only by the deleted pair pool.
    Removed: cause:squadkill payload field killer_squad. Re-resolve via xobject.se(killer_squad_id).
    Removed: cause:alphakill payload fields name, alpha_level, kills. Resolve via xcreature.get_name and ap_ext_tracker.get_alpha_level.
    Renamed: ap_core_utils -> ap_core_util. Singular form, matching ap_ext_util.
    Renamed: payload field total_deaths / death_count -> kill_count on cause:massacre and cause:basekill.
  Internal:
    Changed: news pipeline owns its session FIFO. Activity record removed from broker. Each consequence rolls a chance to publish; on hit, the entry is appended with display strings captured at write time.
    Changed: per-cause RULES and SCAN trace lines emit one log line per attempt at DEBUG. New REASON codes (DISABLED, ON_COOLDOWN, NO_ELIGIBLE_SQUAD, WRONG_PERIOD, BUDGET_EXHAUSTED) distinguish post-filter rejects from scan-empty.
    Changed: needs and instincts pickers no longer silently skip period-mismatched entries at DEBUG. Each off-period sub-cause emits an explicit failed_rules:wrong_period observe line so the funnel includes them; non-DEBUG path is unchanged (entries still skipped without overhead).
    Changed: news compose pipeline observes its own segments. compose / collect / pick_speaker / dispatch nest under one trace. Engine boundary call now timed.
    Changed: HUD funnel split. Per-tick rows: causes -> publishes -> classifies -> executes. Cause-side and consequence-side blocker columns separated.
    Changed: cause-file naming follows generator shape. Singular when one cause is published (reactive), plural when many are (radiant). Consequence files always plural, one file per cause family. 15 consequence files merged to 11.
  Localization:
    Added: 5 EN + 5 RU news templates for the new massacre loot consequence.
    Added: Russian MCM XML rebuilt at parity with English (605 strings).
    Added: Stalker_Boss credited as Russian translator. gwalls credited for English copyediting pass.
    Changed: news templates are per-consequence only. Multi-event composite lines retired (25 ids per locale removed).
    Changed: news voice and time-anchor sweep across EN and RU templates.

1.5.0
  Summary: PDA news system, mutant infestation, additive territory conquest, generative templates, localization (EN+RU), modder API, personality retune
  Gameplay:
    Added: PDA news system. An online stalker on your frequency relays squad activity as radio chatter.
           The framework records every cause and consequence in the simulation as a journal entry.
           News surfaces the journal as emergent gossip, based on how impactful the event is and how relevant the data is for the world.
           Speakers rotate across hearsay, witness, survivor, tracker, and named report.
           Speakers are chosen based on whether they were part of the event, saw the event or proximity to it.
           The news is about the causes, the consequences, or about chained events like a cause generating multiple consequences or consequences leading to other events.
           PDA system reworked around XRAY systems, integrated with existing news queue, respecting emissions, psi-storms, PDA charge, queue cap, and member-only faction channels.
           Visibility of the messages configurable in MCM: own faction, faction and allies, world.
           Rewrote all news text to adapt to the new chained events and to use the data saved in the core broker
    Added: mutant infestation. Feral, predator, and aberrant ALPHAS claim smart terrains as nests. Original spawns are replaced by the infesting species, turning the smart into a single-species lair. (per-map cap configurable in MCM)
    Changed: territory conquest is additive (was exclusive). Conquerors add their faction's spawns alongside the originals instead of replacing them. A conquest produces a mixed zone (vanilla behavior) instead of a clean factional flip.
    Changed: personality values and default ceiling retuned to be more in line with the lore
    Changed: stash fill skips squads at bases. Matches stash loot and stash ambush behavior.
  Core:
    Added: spawn attribution tracing. Every squad spawned by area_conquer or instinct_infest logs with smart, faction, and section when DEBUG is on.
    Added: activity records capture translated display strings for faction, name, and species (subject and other) at write time.
    Changed: All stash causes avoid bases for balance
    Changed: PDA map markers now use a multi-line label with action phrase, "Subject: name (faction)", and "Other: name (faction)" for two-party consequences.
             Markers read pre-translated fields directly from the activity record, so no string resolution at render time.
  MCM:
    Added: News tab. Master toggle, compose interval (1-600 seconds, default 30-100). Scope selector (own / allies / world, default allies). Max age (1-72 game hours, default 12).
    Added: instinct infest settings. Enabled, threshold, rush, personality floor and ceiling.
    Added: infestation mutator settings. Enabled, max per level, spawn count, decay hours.
    Removed: per-consequence PDA chance sliders. News volume is tuned from the News tab.
  Integration:
    Added: activity record API (ap_core_broker).
           record(squad_id, cause, consequence, opts) - write a record
           get_record(opts) - O(1) read for { squad_id, assigned = true }
           get_records(opts) - bulk read
           clear_record(squad_id) - unregister from all systems on entity death
    Added: localized rendering (ap_core_const.CONSEQUENCE_INFO).
           CONSEQUENCE_INFO[consequence] returns { name_key, action_key }
           name_key - short caption ("Massacre Investigate")
           action_key - full action phrase ("Investigating a Massacre Site")
           Both XML ids resolve via game.translate_string. EN and RU ship.
    Added: trace paths.
           ap_core_const.CONSEQUENCE_PHASE - sub-phase identifiers (FIND_TARGETS, MOVE_SQUAD, ARRIVE, etc.)
           ap_core_debug.observe consumes them at DEBUG log level.
    Added: news dispatch (ap_ext_news).
           record_event(subject_squad, cause, consequence, opts) - main entry
           opts.cause_id - groups siblings for paired dispatch
           opts.other_squad - enables two-party templates
           Template pools follow per-consequence, paired, and pattern id conventions.
    Added: spawn injection (xsmart).
           set_shared_spawn(smart, key, identity, num) - alongside originals (conquest pattern)
           set_exclusive_spawn(smart, key, identity, num) - replaces originals (infest pattern)
           Identity accepts stalker factions and mutant species.
    Added: xlibs helpers used by AP.
           xsquad.get_commander_name - commander character_name
           xcreature.get_mutant_species - cached species detection
           xlevel.get_level_name - localized level name from level_id
           xstring.capitalize_first - cp1251-aware first-char uppercase
           xttltable fifo_cache :each + on_evict - bounded cache traversal and eviction hook

  Fixes:
    Fixed: squadkill_revenge chased the player after the player's actor_stalker relation drifted hostile from own-faction kills.
    Fixed: better discovering of player and NPC true community when dispathcing news
    Fixed: Russian MCM News tab strings synced with English.

1.4.0
  Summary: Mutant instincts, pipeline redesign, day/night cycle, food chain, range-based perception, personality recalibration, statistics overlay, integration API
  Gameplay:
    Added: mutant instincts. Five deprivation-scored drives (scatter, feed, sleep, explore, socialize) parallel to stalker needs. Per-instinct xbus routing, Hull drive competition, independent thresholds.
    Changed: mutant personality and alignment redesigned from GSC source (monstry.doc). Species and subspecies detection via xlibs replaces naive community categories.
    Added: food chain. Four behavioral groups (cowardly, feral, predator, aberrant) with tiered avoidance. Cowardly flees feral+predator+aberrant, feral flees predator+aberrant, predator flees aberrant.
    Added: day/night cycle. Stalkers work by day, rest at night. Nocturnal mutants (bloodsuckers, lurkers, chimeras, zombies, fractures) hunt at night, retreat at dawn. All needs and instincts time-gated accordingly.
    Added: range-based perception. EyeRange (200m, vision), RadioRange (500m, stalker PDA), ScentRange (500m, mutant tracking). Each cause type maps to a range tier. Distances derived from empirical smart terrain geometry analysis across 14 levels (nearest-neighbor spacing, vertex density, level dimensions).
    Changed: when an alpha dies, same-species mutants on the level hunt the killer.
    Added: artefact pickup triggers reactions. Outlaws chase the taker. Aberrant mutants converge on the site.
    Changed: decay and cooldown timers use game time (respects time acceleration and realism mods).
  Core:
    Changed: pipeline redesign. Ineligible squads filtered before evaluation budget. Every trigger produces a result.
    Changed: cascading causes with pure predicate gates. Rejections skip expensive queries and immediately try the next cause.
    Added: squad ownership reassertion. Dead squad cleanup. Invalid cause-consequence pairs blocked at cause level.
    Added: statistics overlay. Real-time pipeline metrics (rates, blockers, counts), configurable position via MCM.
    Changed: map markers use blue icons, linger 60s after completion, then fade.
    Changed: general tuning (rush defaults, gulag duration, return-to-simulation timing).
  MCM:
    Added: instincts configuration. Per-instinct toggles, thresholds, and rush settings.
    Added: statistics overlay configuration.
    Added: per-consequence personality floor and ceiling sliders.
  Integration:
    Added: activity record API. record() and get_record() for external mods (e.g. warfare map tooltips).
    Added: PDA marker descriptions via register_descriptions().
    Changed: register_owner() supports override. Integration guide rewritten with current API and examples.
  Compatibility:
    Removed: modded exes requirement. Works with vanilla Anomaly 1.5.3, Demonized, Demonized MT, AOEngine. Tested with GAMMA, EFP, Zona.

1.3.6
  Summary: Hotfix, save compat
  Fixed: updated save migrations. Old scripted squad entries released and rebuilt on load.

1.3.5
  Summary: Alignment system, alpha mutants, reactive chaining, combat mutators, expanded mutant factions
  Gameplay:
    Added: alpha mutants. Mutants that rack up kills become alphas. They hit harder, absorb more punishment, never flee, and drop bonus loot for their species. Scales with kill level. Each feature toggleable in MCM.
    Added: alpha kill retaliation. Killing an alpha triggers same-species mutants to hunt the killer.
    Added: species-based squad death responses. Predator and territorial packs avenge killed members. Herbivores and weak mobs scatter.
    Added: combat mutators via hit callbacks. Alpha hit power scales with kill level. Veteran+ stalker hit power scales from veteran to legend rank. Separate MCM toggles.
    Added: alignment system based on GSC's moral axis (principled, self-serving, unprincipled, outlaw). Military never flees, ecologists never conquer, renegades never investigate etc
    Added: mutant territorial behavior. Mutants conquer territory, avenge their dead, and hunt wounded stalkers based on personality traits.
    Changed: reactive consequences chain. A single event now triggers multiple independent responses. A squad wipe fires both revenge and retreat. A medkit use attracts predators and sends allies to help. A massacre draws scavengers and investigators.
    Changed: personality probability narrowed. Factions commit to identity-consistent behavior more often and hesitate less.
    Changed: squads stay at destinations for realistic durations to let gulag jobs (patrol, sleep, socialize etc) unfold. Previously all squads left after 5 minutes.
    Removed: stalker elites. The engine tracks stalker progression natively through kill-to-rank points.
    Removed: elite kill bounty.
  Core:
    Added: mutators MCM section with toggles for alpha and stalker combat modifiers.
    Added: tracing statistics every minute when debug is on, will help standardise log parsing from users
  i18n:
    Added: full Russian description (doc/readme_ru.txt).
    Fixed: Russian MCM synced with English.
  Fixed:
    Fixed: crash on fast travel when a scripted squad dies offline and the engine recycles its entity ID.

1.3.0
  Summary: Personality system, mutant conquest, territory decay, round-robin dispatch, ownership registry, integration framework, fixes
  Requires xlibs update.

  Gameplay:
    Added: personality profiles for all stalker and mutant factions with trait-driven consequence selection.
    Added: persistent map markers for elite promotion. Marks the elite's squad on the PDA until death.
    Added: squad ownership registry. Alife mods register an ownership filter, AlifePlus skips squads they own. Warfare and BAO registered via legacy proxies.
    Added: integration API for external mods. Register custom causes and consequences without modifying AlifePlus code.
    Added: automatic save data cleanup on version upgrade. Orphaned squads released, stale keys removed.
    Added: conquered territory decays after configurable game hours if not reconquered.
    Added: per-smart cooldown on area cause. Same location cannot trigger conquest repeatedly.
    Changed: each needs consequence tied to specific personality traits. Hunger and sleep use survival, money uses greed, jobs use territory and perception, social uses relation.
    Changed: per-consequence rate budget tightened. The same consequence type cannot dominate a session.
    Changed: post-arrival wait uses game time. Advances during time skips, survives save and load.
    Changed: squads detected as arrived faster (scan interval reduced).
    Changed: stash consequences (loot, ambush, fill) harmonized into the same config-driven pattern as needs.
    Changed: smart terrain mutation and load restore unified into a single periodic update.
    Changed: radiant interval and global consequence budget defaults adjusted for less frequent, more varied activity.
    Removed: job_worship and job_exercise consequences, MCM entries, PDA messages, and item sections.
    Removed: per-consequence chance sliders. Replaced by personality system. PDA chance sliders remain.
  Compatibility:
    Fixed: warfare and BAO ownership filters gave false positives on squads without the expected field.
  Fixed:
    Fixed: area conquest MCM toggle had no effect on previously conquered smart terrains.
    Fixed: radiant causes did not fire on first session after game start.
    Fixed: needs thresholds broke on young saves with low game time.
  Internal:
    Changed: codebase restructured into core (pipeline) and ext (domain).
    Changed: chance gate removal eliminates per-consequence random rolls from every dispatch cycle.
    Changed: protection gate no longer allocates strings below DEBUG log level.
    Changed: producer luabind crossings reduced via global xlibs caching.
    Changed: pacer retries faster on protection reject instead of burning the full interval.
    Changed: radiant and reactive pipelines use independent Bresenham counters. Reactive events no longer biased by radiant traffic volume.
    Added: consumer statistics (PIPELINE, CAUSES, DISPATCH, LIFECYCLE) logged every 60s at DEBUG. Zero cost above DEBUG.
    Changed: alignment and personality checks moved from core consumer to ap_ext_util. Core pipeline has zero domain knowledge.
    Changed: PDA sender selection and message dispatch moved from core to ap_ext_news. Core has zero ext references.
    Changed: all consequence gates (alignment, personality) run inside observe() with full tid/path tracing.
    Changed: guard clause detector recognizes multi-line guards and counts guards throughout the function body.
    Changed: rate limiting reworked with sliding window counters and per-pipeline pacing.
  xlibs (requires xlibs update):
    Added: composite squad protection guard with shared commander context.
    Added: vertex-to-level cache with zero luabind on repeat lookups.
    Changed: scripted check uses engine fields only. Mod-specific fields handled by AP ownership registry.
    Removed: dead code in squad and smart terrain modules.

